      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">Businesses face a near-constant threat of destructive malware,
                ransomware, malicious insider activities, and even honest mistakes that can alter or
                destroy critical data. These data corruption events could cause a significant loss
                to a company s reputation, business operations, and bottom line. These types of
                adverse events, that ultimately impact data integrity, can compromise critical
                corporate information including emails, employee records, financial records, and
                customer data. It is imperative for organizations to recover quickly from a data
                integrity attack and trust the accuracy and precision of the recovered
                data.</abstract>
